Documentation of the database

Everything is available under the http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/ directory. 
so it would be http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/[file name]

why I couldn't use python CGI scripts?
At this moment, I haven't figured out a way to allow the server to listen to the cgi scripts 
since traditionally these scripts are placed within a specific folder named "bin-cgi" or someting
so so far I haven't done so.
php scripts are supposed to be able to do all things possible that can be done with cgi scripts.

To-do: 
 
1. DETAILS field -> 200 characters long? 
2. No LAST_NAME field 
3. PRICE field -> number field
4. Python CGI script to save the recording of the address to a .WAV file out on the server. And it uses the telephone number as the file name. We are also going to need some way to save out the recordings, maybe by order number to a subdirectory.
5. Need three other fields in our database: ORDER_NUM, DATE (which would obviously be a date) and COMPLETED (which would be a Boolean yes/no field). The ORDER_NUM would be used to keep all items of an order together, with a unique number. 
6. to be added...

Schema:

		$table = "CREATE TABLE pizza_order (
		id INT(6) UNSIGNED PRIMARY KEY, 
		item VARCHAR(45) NOT NULL,
		reg_date TIMESTAMP,
		quantity INT(5),
		size VARCHAR(20),
		detail VARCHAR(200),
		price DOUBLE(5,3) NOT NULL,
		completed TINYINT(1))"


===========================================================

How you should have your vxml to post to database directly:

===========================================================

<?xml version="1.0"?>
<vxml version="2.1">
  <form>
    <field name="order" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="order"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
    <field name="item" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="item"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
    <field name="quantity" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="quantity"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
    <field name="size" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="size"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
    <field name="details" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="details"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
    <field name="price" type="digits">
      <filled>
        <submit next="http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php" method="post" namelist="price"/>
      </filled>
    </field>
  </form>
</vxml>

or 

<block>

  <var name="order_num" expr="5"/>

  <var name="item" expr="pizza"/>

  <var name="quantity" expr="1"/>

  <var name="size" expr="large"/>

  <var name="details" expr="['sausage', 'green pepper']"/>

  <var name="price" expr="13.95"/>

  <submit next="url/get.php " method="post" namelist="order_num item quantity size details price" />

</block>




===========================================================

post_form.py 

example python script to post to get.php

===========================================================

# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-
import urllib, urllib2
page = 'http://students.washington.edu/cyc025/db/insert.php'
order = '3'
items = 'pizza'
quantity = '100'
size = 'small'
details = 'cheese'
price = '12'
raw_params = {'order': unicode(order, "utf-8"),'item': unicode(items, "utf-8"),'quantity':unicode(quantity, "utf-8"), 'size':unicode(size, "utf-8"),'details':unicode(details, "utf-8"),'price':unicode(price, "utf-8")}
params = urllib.urlencode(raw_params)
request = urllib2.Request(page, params)
page = urllib2.urlopen(request)
info = page.info()
